<div dir="ltr">Giles,<div><br></div><div>With this latest patch on my &quot;new&quot; system I see</div><div><div>    checking if ConnectX XRC support is enabled... no</div><div>    checking if ConnectIB XRC support is enabled... yes</div></div><div>On a system which had said &quot;yes&quot; for both probes with all previous patches.</div><div>I *think* this is the desired behavior (use the non-deprecated support if both are present).</div><div>However, I am reporting this just in case this was not what you intended.</div><div>I can provide the config.log if you want it.</div><div><br></div><div>On the &quot;old&quot; system I still see the expected</div><div>    checking if ConnectX XRC support is enabled... yes</div><div>    checking if ConnectIB XRC support is enabled... no</div><div><br></div><div>I had no problems compiling the openib btl on either system.</div><div><br></div><div>-Paul</div></div><div class="gmail_extra"><br><div class="gmail_quote">On Sun, Jul 12, 2015 at 7:48 PM, Gilles Gouaillardet <span dir="ltr">&lt;<a href="mailto:gilles@rist.or.jp" target="_blank">gilles@rist.or.jp</a>&gt;</span> wrote:<br><blockquote class="gmail_quote" style="margin:0 0 0 .8ex;border-left:1px #ccc solid;padding-left:1ex">
  
    
  
